ce:section.ce:para:
Method validation followed the International Council on Harmonization (ICH) Q2 R2 guidelines [40], which included linearity and range, limit of detection (LOD), limit of quantitation (LOQ), precision, accuracy, and specificity. The luminescence intensity of the developed NP@CQDs at the emission wavelength of 420 nm was measured before and after adding increasing concentrations of GSH. The method demonstrated good linearity over the range of 0.5–10 µg/mL, with a correlation coefficient (r) of 0.9967 (Table 1
                        ). LOD and LOQ were visually examined, with LOD representing the lowest amount of the analyte that could be consistently identified. LOQ denotes the lowest concentration that can be determined with adequate precision and accuracy. LOD and LOQ were found to be 0.16 and 0.50 µg/mL, respectively. The method's accuracy was assessed by triplicate determination of three distinct concentrations (2, 4, 7 µg/mL) within the linear range. The mean % recoveries were within the permitted compendial range, indicating the method's accuracy. Triplicate determinations of three distinct concentrations were used on the same day and over three consecutive days to test intra- and inter-day precision. The acquired results demonstrated an acceptable RSD of less than 2 % (Table 2
                        ).
